TextBlock.TextLine: yd expiriency will teach you the needfull, I hope each packett comes to
yd handes as I send itt & then you will see, the fine ness off itt I have now no
more laces, except a few curious newest pattarnes which are up on the cussons
& will not be ready before towards which time exspect allarrived &
most part sold off to content & ta finde a further or dernnew instructions
for the longer I doitt the better itt will succed & where as others must allow
3 a 4 pr for buying in & fould ing, I do itt mij self & have the laces from
the worck wemen selfs so that I rekon can advance the provision note
that way, where fore am of opinion to have them as cheapas ett can
be exspected from any other hand what sosver: I have here a fabrieck of
tijkes which are much demanded in England & have some thoughts, that
wee could fould a good parcell in them now & then, for thought the
packes be opened att arrivall in the custome house yett I do not beleanc
that they open & insold thetykes, which pray in forme yd self of
privately & in case you can dispose of tykes could send now & then
a pack for returnes itt beeing a como much demanded in England & of
which I have constant orders from m John loyd & others which must
remitt. their monyes to that purpose, so that you beeng in the least
in corridged qive mee yd orders & I shall endeavour to incorridgetae
continuancy of our correspondency my next shall carry all acctt. of
sale to mr. Cole & then thinck they will finde some moresatis
faction for I have the least thoughts not to dowell to him or his relations
that hathe been so kinde to mee of which you & freinds may be intunatey
assured whilst I rest with kinde salute
In Antwerp 22 feb
London Henry Maynard
th
S my last to you was on the 18: curitt sence recd. yd of 9 ditto yd bill for
the ballance of my last acctt. shall be punctually discharged, so that
our acctt beginnes with the 2 new bales 1& 2 of the catter finding
now the invoyce & pattarnes, rekon there will be broewne culs enought
sothat the brownest might be onely acurrious gold & bluck menture
the rest as desired & to that soutt sent last, because I feare with the
summer so mony browne would lijd on hand so that itt will be nessecay
to assort the rest with the most pleasants iullours you kan finde as desired
there is fl. hath send some curious new assortement to one hoosendael
here is cheef corespondent & a greind of mine that saco the patt
sold mee he neser saw so curious pattarnes wherefore lett mee intreat
you to be very curious exact in the rest of desired spanish cloathes
nay for feare of a miss, in answer here off send mee what new pass
now are come out whilst in the meand while you shall be aproviding
of the 2 following packs spanish cloathes in which no pleasant light
lively drap cullours may be neglected. I have in ordered a fers mocts
to them to be added 3 blew cloathes viz one of the lightest sort an
other of scome what brouwner & athird of the brownest blew sort
& of the best sort of 5:10 a 6 a 64 penie ayd the mochs & bles
to be one bale besides desire you to provide 6 demy cottons red of the
bestcullours in prijses of 25 a 26 pence a goad white an dan other
coschester bay which I have found by other in voyces cost about 23 a 2½
pence p yd, whoever provide that as best you ian & lett itt be sent with
the redcottons in which in scawen will pack somd callicons
you will gett the devonshire & swanskins bayes which is well I hope
you shall have bought the fine ones of spanish woolmentioned bon
before & inclased in the same parcell hence forward shall remitt for yd
acctt. as best I can & exspect the whites pr. first & seeng they are so deare
must advance here acfordingly as soone I shall receave the goods in ordered
from the north shall be able to advise you whom to stich to for the future
& so remaine
this amiddling blew one must be lighter an other
to & the 3 browne
In Antwarp 22 feb
London Henry Collier
th
S in answer to both yd of 4 & 7: curitt TH. will be suld next week with all
rigour possible, till an to the 2 bills the procuroud, s hould have proceeded
this week butt thath been indisposed & now recovered: John Pickley hath
been att bruges well 2 months & this day sace hin on the exd. againe
I exspected yd small pack of cloathes here yett this day & hope to dispose
of y sudd amly because of late non arrived & these will moy the new
dcties: I observe you will furnish a small pack of cloathes, I could wish to ave
some thing needs & curious for I kent hath sent some to his freind roosendael
which I understand are rare, & not knowing what news there might he
in fine goods could wish you might match not onely the patt. outt
some more thing rare besides, of which then see the pat. shall give you
my opinion you bill for £200: shall finde acceptance butt pray lett
that be the last for yett a while the in closed please to deliver & & in case
he begon, returne tomee & you will obligee
In Antwarp 22 feb1
London Rich. Southell
th
S. my last to you was on the 18: curitt sence recd. yd of y ditto when you
in these contreys againe att our meeting wee will settle all things
knowing you will do yd ut most to promots yd as well as my intest
whilst you be in England: if you approve of itt I may order in maynad
2 pack ortwo of northrens butt I doubt itt will not do neither Iam
sensible of mr. Chippings dead for I doubt A.V. will not be able to serve
my turnes that I must finde out some other freind in the north, sell
m. Annes lay not to omitt the s½yd white perpetuanes Itake notue
of the atte station you sent mee where in I observe nemine contradac
ente well how would you have mee only contradict itt nay thougg
itt had been as much againe, butt whilst itt is no more pray lett itt
so& vemember mee to all freinds & asseure them that I am thew
London thom led gin ghem
th
In Antwarp 2 ½ d 1681
S. in answer to yd of 22 pas. desire you to provide in peces of 12 yds
white perpetuanios, as now twice you bought for mee & do yd ut most to send
good substantiall broad goods & make y up in apais to be shipt off att exon there
beingnossa versel ready the valess you will finde by in Arthur Annessay
mo
as the last pray dispach I. as soonas possible & you will oblige
Brugge Raphael Coots
In Antwerpen 24 feb 681
Mijn h. in antwoort vanden ul van 19 deser referre aen mijn twee
van 17 ditto den welke geloove p voerman beneffens het paxken cante
N12, ul sal sijn geworden ul respice wegens het paxken gout van 12 dese
is maer eerst over 4 dagien mij geworden also den bode het selve niet
af sendeten sijde weirde daer voordaen ontfangen satuydagh savonts
is mij het pack A8N. 22 p voerman geworden hadde gewenst
N 21 daer bij hadde geweest alsoo den om d'ander noodigh hebbe nochtas
verwaght hedenp Jan dobbelaer tselve sal arriveeren beneffens de
doij andere packen ofte anders mij peeiudice sal bij brengen, oversh
ditto dobbelaet vertrocken sijnde & dat Ben: clarck eert daernae
costij was aencomen sal sal ul deselve packen p barijen
